==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} *{{term||overheren|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|oferhieran|oferhīeran|to overhear, hear, disobey, disregard, neglect|lang=ang}}, equivalent to {{prefix|over|hear}}. Cognate with {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|overhoren||to hear, hear about|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|überhören||to not hear, ignore|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} {{term|overhøre||to overhear|lang=da}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈovəɻhiɻ/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|overhears|overhearing|overheard}}

# To [[hear]] something that wasn't meant for one's ears.

